    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is RF Micro different from regular microneedling?",
            "answer": "<p>RF microneedling combines precision microneedling with radiofrequency energy delivered beneath the surface of the skin. While traditional microneedling stimulates surface collagen, RF allows controlled energy delivery into the dermis for deeper, more targeted structural remodelling.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does RF Microneedling hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients describe the treatment as tolerable. A topical numbing cream is applied beforehand to maximise comfort. You may feel warmth or pressure during treatment, but discomfort is typically mild and short-lived.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does the skin look like immediately after treatment?",
            "answer": "<p>The skin may appear mildly red or warm, similar to light sun exposure. Redness usually settles within 24–48 hours depending on treatment depth.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions do I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients benefit from a course of 3–6 sessions spaced 4–6 weeks apart. The exact number depends on your skin condition, goals, and treatment depth.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Early improvements in skin texture may be visible within 2–3 weeks. Collagen production continues to increase over several months, with progressive improvements in firmness and tone.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results can last many months, especially when delivered as a structured course. Maintenance treatments may be recommended depending on your skin goals and ageing profile.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients experience mild social downtime of 24–48 hours. Light dryness or flaking may occur in the days following treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is RF Microneedling safe for all skin types?",
            "answer": "<p>RF microneedling is suitable for most skin types when assessed and delivered correctly. Suitability is confirmed during your consultation and medical review.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who should avoid RF Microneedling?",
            "answer": "<p>Treatment may not be suitable if you:</p><p>• Are pregnant or breastfeeding</p><p>• Have active skin infections or open wounds</p><p>• Have certain implanted electronic devices</p><p>• Have a history of abnormal scarring (assessed individually)</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>You may experience mild redness and a warm sensation for 24–48 hours, similar to a light sunburn. Most people return to their normal routine the next day. Makeup can typically be applied after 24 hours.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is RF Microneedling suitable for all skin types?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes - RF Microneedling is safe for all skin tones and types, and is fully customisable by depth and intensity.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need to book a consultation before my first session?",
            "answer": "<p>No you don't your consultation is done on the day of your treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment will receive a full refund or can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day can be rescheduled but will not be refunded.<br/><br/>If you do not show to your appointment you will not receive a refund or a reschedule. Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens if you determine the treatment is not for me?",
            "answer": "<p>You will be issued a full refund.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long after my first treatment before I can have my second one?",
            "answer": "<p>We usually recommend waiting 4 to 6 weeks between RF Microneedling sessions.</p><p>This allows your skin time to fully heal and for new collagen to form before your next treatment, helping you achieve the best possible results.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many RF Microneedling sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>For the best and longest-lasting results, we typically recommend a course of 3 to 4 sessions, spaced 4 to 6 weeks apart.</p><p>This gives your skin time to naturally rebuild collagen and elastin between treatments, creating smoother, firmer, more youthful results that continue to improve over time.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
